<paragraph id="326B36F7FF9B5434FF49276BFF0BFC73" blockId="4.[151,1436,778,964]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
The genus 
<taxonomicName id="F5D44D74FF9B5434FEF8276BFE5CFC94" box="[294,426,778,803]" class="Insecta" family="Eriococcidae" genus="Eriococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="00A0EAE5FF9B5434FEF8276BFE5CFC94" box="[294,426,778,803]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Eriococcus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
currently contains several hundred species and is almost certainly paraphyletic, although the defining characters for possible generic divisions are still uncertain. 
<collectingCountry id="4AC37667FF9B5434FBB02753FB78FCFB" box="[1134,1166,818,844]" name="American Samoa" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">As</collectingCountry>
indicated in the Introduction, 
<bibRefCitation id="56454B06FF9B5434FF23273BFE24FCC3" box="[253,466,858,884]" pageId="4" pageNumber="14" refString="Cook, L. G., Gullan, P. J. &amp; Trueman, H. E. (2002) A preliminary phylogeny of the scale insects (Hemiptera: Sternorrhyncha: Coccoidea) based on nuclear small-subunit ribosomal DNA. Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution, 25, 43 - 52." type="journal article">
Cook 
<emphasis id="00A0EAE5FF9B5434FE9D273BFE8BFCC4" box="[323,381,858,883]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">et al.</emphasis>
(
<number id="841C24D0FF9B5434FE52273BFE3CFCC3" box="[396,458,858,884]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="2002.0">2002</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
consider that species in this genus fall within three quite separate clades. The relationships of the species described as new below is unknown but is morphologically similar to 
<taxonomicName id="F5D44D74FF9B5434FB2627E3FF0BFC73" authority="Maskell." authorityName="Maskell." class="Insecta" family="Eriococcidae" genus="Eriococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="araucariae">
<emphasis id="00A0EAE5FF9B5434FB2627E3FA6AFC2C" box="[1272,1436,898,923]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">E. araucariae</emphasis>
Maskell.
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
